(firstQuint)Efficacy of Daily Vitamin D3 Supplementation in Normal Weight Adolescents.

 Twenty normal weight adolescents between ages 12-18 that are age and gender would receive vitamin D3 supplementation at a dose of 2000 IU/day.

 Levels of 25(OH)vitamin D would be measured at baseline and after 12 weeks.

Relationship between 25 OH vitamin D levels and other demographic variables will be assessed.

The primary endpoint in this study is the 25 OH Vitamin D level at 12 weeks.

